pageContext.claim: “Over the past three months, the United States has surpassed market expectations by a total of 12 million new jobs. Over the last three months, the United States has added 623,000 manufacturing jobs.”
pageContext.analysis: The U.S. regained 650,000 manufacturing jobs since April when more than a million were lost. In other words, the total number of manufacturing jobs has not rebounded to pre-pandemic levels.
